text: Vesta is an unincorporated community in Grays Harbor County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Vesta was established in 1892, and remained in operation until 1936. The community was named after Vesta Dwinelle, the wife of a local pioneer. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Grays Harbor County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Vesta, Washington
